    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>This recipe takes around 5-10 min to prep, so get your casserole dish and all your ingredients ready, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Make sure your dish is oven-proof and safe to use on the hob. Don't have one? Start cooking in a large, wide-based pan then transfer to an oven-proof dish and cover tightly with foil</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-pork-shoulder-ragu/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based <strong>hob-safe</strong> <strong>oven-proof casserole dish</strong> with a matching lid with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>diced pork shoulder </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until lightly browned</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-pork-shoulder-ragu/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and roughly dice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Top, tail and chop your <strong>carrot[s]</strong> roughly</p><p>Peel and roughly chop your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-pork-shoulder-ragu/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the pork is browned, add the <strong>diced onion</strong>, <strong>chopped carrot </strong>and <strong>garlic </strong>with your <strong>dried</strong> <strong>oregano </strong>and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-pork-shoulder-ragu/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant add your <strong>chopped tomatoes </strong>and <strong>chicken stock mix </strong>with 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[200ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>and a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Season with a generous grind of <strong>pepper </strong>and add your <strong>soy sauce</strong>, <strong>Henderson's relish </strong>and <strong>tomato paste </strong>and and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cover with the lid and put the dish in the oven for 30 min or until the sauce has reduced slightly</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-pork-shoulder-ragu/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>After an initial 30 min, add your <strong>pasta </strong>to the pot with 400ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[520ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[680ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> and stir it all together</p><p>Return the dish to the oven for a final 25-30 min or until the sauce has thickened, the pork is cooked through and the pasta is tender</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-pork-shoulder-ragu/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the pasta is tender, remove the dish from the oven and add <strong>half </strong>your <strong>grated</strong> <strong>Italian hard cheese </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) with a little <strong>salt</strong>,<strong> </strong>then give everything a good mix up</p><p>Allow to rest, covered, for 5 mins \u2013 this is your <strong>one pot pork shoulder rag\u00f9</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-pork-shoulder-ragu/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>one pot pork shoulder rag\u00f9 </strong>and sprinkle with the <strong>remaining grated Italian hard cheese</strong></p><p>Finish with a generous grind of <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Dig in!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
